 Opening 
This is an opportunity for entrepreneurial scientists to start and lead new R&D areas as a Principal Investigator at BBN Technologies. Successful candidates will have the opportunity to explore their own research agendas, organize and direct teams of bright scientists and engineers, and do important work.
 
 
Who we are 
For more than 70 years, scientists and engineers in diverse disciplines at BBN Technologies have collaborated to solve real-world problems through research, exploration, development and prototyping. We partner with the best technical talent in academia and industry to challenge the status quo, pioneer new technologies, and create transformative solutions.
 
 
Our creative teams take pride in their work and tackle exceptionally hard problems to provide useful, practical solutions for our customers. We are one of the nation's premier research and development laboratories, awarded the 2011 National Medal of Technology and Innovation by the President of the United States ‚Äúfor sustained innovation through the engineering of first-of-a-kind, practical systems‚Äù. 
 
What you will do
 
We're looking for experienced, creative, entrepreneurial, and highly motivated research leaders who can hit the ground running, interact with customers and potential customers, obtain funding for projects, organize and lead project teams, and lead the growth of current and new research areas.
 
 
BBN excels at very high-end R&D. Our current areas of technical interest and expertise are: 
 
Analytics / Forecasting 
Artificial Intelligence / Semantic reasoning / Machine Learning 
Autonomy / Collaborative swarm behaviors 
Command & Control 
Computational imaging 
Cyber Security / Cyber Physical 
Distributed Systems 
Logistics 
Next-generation Networking and Communications 
Non-traditional computing 
Photonic integrated circuits 
Positioning, Navigation and Timing 
Quantum Information Processing 
Sensor Systems / Lidar / Radar / Undersea acoustics 
Speech, Language & Multimedia 
Synthetic Biology / Biotechnology 
 
What you need
 
 Outstanding record of technology innovation and leadership Demonstrated excellence in interacting with customers and decision-makers Proven track record in writing successful proposals, standing up research teams, and executing projects successfully Creativity and entrepreneurial streak
 Advanced degree required. 
Additional Skills that would be AWESOME 
This position requires the eligibility to obtain a security clearance. Except in rare circumstances, only U.S. citizens are eligible for a security clearance. 
 
Why Us
 
Our team members are passionate about growth, innovation and collaboration. We are constantly striving to improve and better ourselves so that we can better support our clients.
 
Our culture enables all employees to find purpose, thrive, and succeed. By creating an environment where all opinions are valued, risk taking is encouraged, and excellence is rewarded, we allow our employees to do their best, most important work.
 
If you have a growth mindset and you thrive under pressure, Come Join Our Team!
 
 
